<div class="policy-container">
  <h1>Logging Policy</h1>
  <p>Last updated: December 14, 2025</p>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Our Strict No-Logs Policy</h2>
    <p>We operate a strict no-logs policy, meaning we do not collect, store, or monitor any information about your online activities while using our service. This includes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your browsing history or visited websites</li>
      <li>Traffic destinations, data content, or DNS queries</li>
      <li>Original IP addresses or assigned VPN IP addresses</li>
      <li>Connection timestamps or session durations</li>
      <li>Bandwidth usage per individual session</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Minimal Data for Service Operation</h2>
    <p>To maintain and improve the service, we may collect limited, anonymized aggregated data, such as total server load or overall connection counts. This data cannot be linked to any individual user or account.</p>
    <p>Any temporary technical data required for troubleshooting or performance (e.g., crash reports) is anonymized and deleted within 24 hours.</p>
    <p>We do not store payment details directly; payments are processed through trusted third-party providers.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Commitment to Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our infrastructure is designed to minimize data retention. Servers operate in a way that prevents persistent logging of user-specific information.</p>
    <p>We are committed to transparency and may pursue independent third-party audits in the future to verify our no-logs policy.</p>
    <p>This policy applies to all users, ensuring your privacy is protected at all times.</p>
  </section>
</div>

